Manifestation of childhood Hodgkin's disease and Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma differ, especially in the latter, from those in adults. Extranodal involvement is seen even more frequently in childhood Non-Hodgkin's lymphomas than in adults. This article reviews the radiological findings in malignant lymphomas in children, explains the differences in the manifestation of Hodgkin's disease and Non-Hodgkin's lymphomas, of different subtypes and of the malignant lymphomas in adults. The problems in diagnosis of organ manifestation and special problems of diagnostic imaging procedures in children are discussed.  
